OL,3,CMiners' strike at 40: What were the
OL,4,Ckey dates for the North East?
OL,6,FIn brief: What happened and when?
OL,8,F5 March 1984 - Unofficial strike
OL,9,Faction began when miners in
OL,10,FCortonwood, South Yorkshire, voted to
OL,11,Fwalk out over a decision to close
OL,12,Ftheir pit.
OL,14,F6 March 1984 - The National Coal Board
OL,15,Fannounced its plan to close 20
OL,16,Fcollieries, which would have resulted
OL,17,Fin the loss of 20,00 jobs.
