OL,3,CMiners' strike at 40: What were the
OL,4,Ckey dates for the North East?
OL,6,F12 March 1984 - The National Union of
OL,7,FMineworkers (NUM), declare a national
OL,8,Fstrike - although no national vote was
OL,9,Fheld.
OL,11,FEasington, in County Durham, was the
OL,12,Ffirst pit in the Durham coalfield to
OL,13,Fjoin the strike. Others followed suit
OL,14,Fin Durham and in Northumberland.
OL,16,FApril to June 1984 - Violence flared
OL,17,Fon picket lines, erupting at the
OL,18,Fbattle of Orgreave, in Rotherham, on
OL,19,F18 June. Hundreds of riot police
OL,20,Fbrutally clashed with miners, some
OL,21,Ffrom the North East.
