OL,3,CMiners' strike at 40: What were the
OL,4,Ckey dates for the North East?
OL,6,FJuly 1984 - Margaret Thatcher
OL,7,Fdescribed the miners as "the enemy
OL,8,Fwithin".
OL,10,FAugust 1984 - One miner crosses the
OL,11,Fpicket line in Easington. For weeks it
OL,12,Fbecomes a village under siege.
OL,14,FSeptember 1984 - The strike was ruled
OL,15,Fillegal in September 1984, as no
OL,16,Fnational ballot of the NUM had been
OL,17,Fheld.
OL,19,FSeptember 1984 to February 1985 -
OL,20,FWinter sets in. More men cross the
OL,21,Fpicket lines, causing bitter division.
